result.execSummary:
The defendant Clinton Dale Barnes-Shaw was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Clinton Dale Barnes-Shaw is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Clinton Dale Barnes-Shaw was found guilty of Possess Methamphetamine Precursors [Modifiers: Second and Subsequent Offense], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.65.
  • Clinton Dale Barnes-Shaw was found guilty of Possess Drug Paraphernalia to Manufacture, Compound, Convert, Produce, or Store Methamphetamine [Modifiers: Second and Subsequent Offense], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(3)(a).
